One of the Beauchêne brothers, Léon diligently attends guests at the front of house. His eyes light up for each customer and a brilliant smile accompanies his thick Cormyrian accent.
A copy of this item (including any crafting you do on it) is used by your Bottled Companion.

The second eldest son of the Beauchêne family, Basile is a true prodigy in the kitchen. He works diligently with his father, determined to become as great as the patriarch one day.

((Job System Trainer))

A Cormyrian wine-smith, Antione is the eldest brother of the Beauchêne family. He handles most of the wine and other drinks that come through the restaurant.

((Job System Trainer))

The head chef of this fine establishment, Mathéo is the patriarch of the Beauchêne family. He is hard on his family and workers, but at the end of the day he'll join in on the merriment. Laugh lines around his eyes make it clear he's only all-business in the kitchen.

Value.value: Out of the kitchen! We are working!
It is too busy here. Please go. You can take one of the cookies, but no other free samples!

value.0:
Léonie is the only daughter in the Beauchêne family and she has always been a bit spoiled by her many brothers and doting father, especially after their mother died. Still, she wanted to help out with the business. She just takes frequent breaks.

She looks like she could be dozing off and smells just slightly of Saint-Lilou.

value.0: The head server of the bistro, Clément expertly navigates even the busiest of mealtimes. He is the youngest brother in the family and well-known as a bit of a charmer.

Value.value: Beauchêne Rouge is a luxurious Cormyrian wine created by the Beauchêne family. The sweet wine smells of both grapes and cherries and has a strong flavor that pairs well with pork.

value.0: It seems the bistro kitchen staff will allow you to get some Chateau Beauchêne fresh from the casket - at an elevated price. The golden wine is the bistro's finest offering.

Value.value: Chateau Beauchêne is a high-end, aromatic wine with a golden coloration. Notes of peach and lychee are present alongside a variety of spices. It makes for an exotic, nuanced flavor that pairs well with seafood.
